    "receivedRecommendations": [
      {
        "givenBy": "Manas Talukdar",
        "givenByHeadline": "Builder | VP of Engineering | AI, Large-scale systems | Senior Fellow",
        "givenAt": "December 21, 2023, Manas managed Dylan directly",
        "givenByLink": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/manastalukdar",
        "description": "Dylan was part of my organization at C3 AI. He joined us straight out of grad school, a few months before I came onboard. His competence and confidence stood out to me even as I was ramping up and getting to know the lay of the land. Around that time Dylan played a key role for a critical initiative, helping the company reach an important milestone for a major release. I was impressed by his high technical strength, and ability to deliver on time while also absorbing new areas. With organizational growth and new projects, it was an easy decision for me to make Dylan the technical lead for a new engineering team in my org, working on a greenfield project at the intersection of data infrastructure and machine learning.\n\nDylan did a spectacular job in being the technical fulcrum for that team. He worked well with senior architects, data scientists and other stakeholders. He was instrumental in our engagement with an external startup while researching integration with their product. He was meticulous in documentation as well as project management. He wrote high-quality code and was actively involved in design decisions with senior architects. Dylan also did a great job in mentoring and coaching several new engineers in that team. He helped them ramp up and enabled them to be successful. He played a key role in keeping morale high. While the team did not have a dedicated engineering manager at that time, the gap was never felt thanks to his multifaceted talents.\n\nI have no hesitation in saying that Dylan exhibited exceptional drive, competency and leadership abilities. I wholeheartedly recommend him and would welcome the opportunity to work together again. Dylan would be a great asset for any organization!",
